# Git workflow

## Branches

| Branch | Role |
|--------|------|
| `main` | Production-ready; deploys `polytryhard-main` |
| `staging` | Integration / user-test; deploys `polytryhard-staging` |
| `feat/*`, `fix/*`, `docs/*`, `refactor/*` | Short-lived work branches |

`staging` is a **long-lived** branch. Do not delete it after merges.

## Rules

1. **All feature work** branches from `staging`, not `main`.
2. **Open PRs** (never merge locally without a PR unless the user explicitly asks otherwise).
3. **Feature PR base:** `staging`. One completed **Linear issue → one PR** into `staging`.
4. **Release PR:** after staging soak / user testing, open a PR **`staging` → `main`**. Do not cherry-pick feature commits onto `main`.
5. **Commits:** conventional prefixes (`feat/`, `fix/`, …); include AI co-author line when assisted.

## Agent checklist (new work)

```bash
git fetch origin
git checkout staging && git pull origin staging
git checkout -b feat/<linear-id>-<short-slug>   # e.g. feat/POL-42-settings-nav
# … implement …
git push -u origin HEAD
gh pr create --base staging --title "…" --body "…"
```

Linear ID in the branch name when an issue exists; link the issue in the PR body.

## Promotion to main

Only after the user confirms staging is good:

```bash
gh pr create --base main --head staging --title "Promote staging to main" …
```

Merge via GitHub UI or `gh pr merge` after review — not `git merge` on `main` without a PR.

## Do not

- Open feature PRs against `main`.
- Push directly to `staging` or `main` (unless user explicitly requests a hotfix exception).
- Rebase `staging` onto `main` routinely; promotion is `staging` → `main` via PR.

See `docs/PDD.md` §9.1 for deployment pairing (branch ↔ Coolify service).
